rules: Rule1: If nausea is a symptom, then headache is a symptom.
Rule2: Provided that fever is a symptom, nausea is a symptom.
Rule3: Whenever the diagnosis is preliminary, then if the absence of food W being consumed implies that food W is digested, fever is a symptom.
Rule4: Either the diagnosis is preliminary or the diagnosis is final.
Rule5: Under the condition that the diagnosis is final, if the failure of food W being consumed to lead to its digestion occurs, then fever is a symptom.
Rule6: Either region Z is under quarantine, or if substance X is recalled, then substance X is contaminated.
Rule7: Whenever region Z is under lockdown, a curfew is in place in region Z.
Rule8: Under the condition that region Z is under lockdown, movement in region Z is not restricted.
Rule9: Either region Z is under lockdown, or region Z is not under quarantine.
Rule10: Provided that a curfew is in place in region Z, a travel ban is imposed on region Z.
Rule11: Whenever there is an outbreak of disease Y in region Z, disease Y is spreading in region Z.
Rule12: If a travel ban is imposed on region Z, then movement in region Z is restricted.
Rule13: Provided that an inspection is conducted on food W, if there is an outbreak of disease Y in region Z, then whenever regulation is not enforced, substance X is contaminated.
Rule14: If distribution is licensed, then distribution is permitted.
Rule15: If vomiting is a symptom, then headache is a symptom.
Rule16: Provided that an antiemetic is dispensed, an antiemetic is prescribed.
Rule17: Whenever disease Y is spreading in region Z, disease Y has reached epidemic status.

Rule18: If the initial protocol is in use, then in the case that the negation of the implication that the absence of food W being consumed implies that food W is digested leads to vomiting not being a symptom, and antiemetic treatment is not administered, an antiemetic is dispensed.

Rule19: Provided that the revised protocol is in use, if the failure of the negation of the implication that the absence of food W being consumed implies that food W is digested to result in vomiting being a symptom leads to antiemetic treatment not being administered, then an antiemetic is dispensed.
Rule20: If preventive measures are implemented, then in the event that neither the initial protocol nor the revised protocol is in use, containment guidelines exist.
Rule21: Either preventive measures are implemented, or reactive measures are implemented.
Rule22: Under the condition that reactive measures are implemented, if it is not the case that either the initial protocol or the revised protocol is in use, then containment guidelines exist.
Rule23: Provided that chills are a symptom, fever is a symptom.
Rule24: If patient P is hospitalized, then patient P is not isolated.
Rule25: Whenever patient P is in intensive care, patient P is hospitalized.
Rule26: If disease Y has reached epidemic status, then under the condition that regulation is not enforced, substance X is contaminated.
Rule27: Provided that hygiene practice G is maintained, patient P is not discharged.
Rule28: If worker K has received training, then hygiene practice G is maintained.
Rule29: Either worker K has received training, or worker K is certified.
Rule30: Provided that routine screening is performed, laboratory testing is conducted.
Rule31: Either routine screening is performed, or targeted screening is performed.
Rule32: Under the condition that targeted screening is performed, if food W is consumed, food W is digested.
Rule33: Provided that laboratory testing is conducted, laboratory analysis is performed.
Rule34: Either an exemption from compliance is granted, or if compliance with regulations is achieved, then if laboratory analysis is performed, then whenever food W is consumed, food W is digested.
Rule35: If food W is safe, then regulation is enforced.
Rule36: Provided that food W is approved, regulation is enforced.
Rule37: If food W has been tested, then food W is safe.
Rule38: Either food W has been tested, or food W has been consumed.
Rule39: If food W has been digested, then food W is approved.
Rule40: If it is not the case that worker K being certified implies hygiene practice G is maintained, then protocol H has been violated.
Rule41: Under the condition that the absence of food W being consumed does not lead to food W being digested, headache is not a symptom.
Rule42: Provided that the failure of the negation of the implication from an investigation on food W to an inspection on food W to result in food W having clearance occurs, distribution is licensed.
Rule43: If it is not the case that the negation of the implication from an investigation on food W to an inspection on food W implies food W has clearance, then distribution is not permitted.

Rule44: Under the condition that the negation of the implication from the absence of food W being consumed to its digestion does not lead to vomiting being a symptom, antiemetic treatment is administered.
Rule45: Whenever the negation of the implication from the lack of food W consumption to its digestion does not imply chills are a symptom, patient P is isolated.

Rule46: Under the condition that the negation of the implication that the negation of the implication from food W not being consumed to it being digested results in vomiting being a symptom does not imply antiemetic treatment is not administered, an antiemetic is not prescribed.

Rule47: If the negation of the implication that the negation of the implication from food W not being consumed to it being digested leads to chills being a symptom does not result in patient P being in intensive care, then patient P is discharged.
Rule48: If regulation is not enforced, then substance X is recalled.
Rule49: Under the condition that regulation is not enforced, substance X is not contaminated.
facts: Fact1: There is an outbreak of disease Y in region Z.
Fact2: An investigation is underway on food W.
Fact3: Compliance with regulations is achieved.
Fact4: Food W does not have clearance.
Fact5: Containment guidelines do not exist.
Fact6: Protocol H has not been violated.
Fact7: An exemption from compliance is not granted.
